    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1916-06-15T16:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1916-06-15T16:00:00-05:00" n="397"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d397">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 711.38/83</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to Chargé
                            <persName type="to">Scholle</persName>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1916-06-15T16:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">June 15, 1916, 4 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Haitian Minister informs Department Commission has been recalled. Congress having
                    passed bill authorizing American Naval and Marine officers to serve with Haitian
                    constabulary, amended agreement embodying recommendation of Major Butler has
                    been submitted to Commission. Bank agreement merely awaits formal signature and
                    Railroad’s argument has been presented.</p>
                <p>Request that Minister be immediately and definitively instructed to conduct and
                    conclude these negotiations. Cooperate with Butler who may materially assist in
                    obtaining consent to desired changes in Constabulary agreement. Department
                    believes, however, that Engineer of Public Works cannot properly be included
                    therein, but will recommend naval officer for that position.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
